The paper deals with learning-based hashing techniques for multimedia search, which involves computer vision (CV) and multimedia (MM) processing. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning-based hashing methods, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel loss function, which involves semantic understanding and attention mechanisms, which falls under the category of information retrieval (IR). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG, and cs.AI.
